meta_info.name: FEEDER_AUDIT
meta_info.description: The `FEEDER_AUDIT` class defines the semantics of an audit trail which is constructed to describe the origin of data that have been transformed into openEHR form and committed to the system.

attributes.name: originating_system_item_ids
attributes.description: Identifiers used for the item in the originating system, e.g. filler and placer ids.

attributes.name: feeder_system_item_ids
attributes.description: Identifiers used for the item in the feeder system, where the feeder system is distinct from the originating system.

attributes.name: original_content
attributes.description: Optional inline inclusion of or reference to original content corresponding to the openEHR content at this node. Typically a URI reference to a document or message in a persistent store associated with the EHR.

attributes.name: originating_system_audit
attributes.description: Any audit information for the information item from the originating system.

attributes.name: feeder_system_audit
attributes.description: Any audit information for the information item from the feeder system, if different from the originating system.
